The paper proposes a game-theoretic framework to incentivize users of data centers to participate in demand response programs. This involves modeling the interactions between the data center and its users, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also focuses on reducing energy consumption in data centers, which is a key concern in the field of data centers (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of two other emerging demand response strategies, server shutdown and local renewable energy generation, which are relevant to the fields of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), systems (cs.SY), and software engineering (cs.SE).
